programme.title: Dossier Eredivisie
programme.desc: In de derde aflevering staat de kopbal centraal. Van alle doelpunten in de Eredivisie wordt maar liefst 15% met het hoofd gemaakt. Van alle balcontacten tijdens een voetbalwedstrijd zijn er gemiddeld 7,7% met het hoofd. Dat betekent dat er tijdens 1 Eredivisieseizoen maar liefst 28.000 keer wordt gekopt. Het is ook al jaren bekend dat koppen niet goed is voor de gezondheid. Het verhoogt de kans op ALS, de ziekte van Parkinson en dementie.

programme.desc: In de derde aflevering staat de kopbal centraal. Van alle doelpunten in de Eredivisie wordt maar liefst 15% met het hoofd gemaakt. Van alle balcontacten tijdens een voetbalwedstrijd zijn er gemiddeld 7,7% met het hoofd. Dat betekent dat er tijdens 1 Eredivisieseizoen maar liefst 28.000 keer wordt gekopt. Het is ook al jaren bekend dat koppen niet goed is voor de gezondheid. Het verhoogt de kans op ALS, de ziekte van Parkinson en dementie.

programme.desc: The official film of the 2019 PGA Championship from the Bethpage Black Course in New York. Brooks Koepka came into the event looking to defend his title from 2018.

programme.title: PGA Championship Official Film2020

programme.title: PGA Championship Official Film2021
programme.desc: The official film of the 2021 PGA Championship, a tournament miraculously won by a 50-year-old Phil Mickelson who surpassed Julius Boros to become the oldest men's player to win a Major.

programme.title: PGA Championship Official Film2022
programme.desc: The official film of the 2022 PGA Championship, a year that belonged to Justin Thomas, as the American pipped his compatriot Will Zalatoris in a playoff at Southern Hills Country Club.

programme.title: PGA Championship Official Film2023
programme.desc: The official film of the 2023 PGA Championship, as Oak Hill Country Club took centre stage once more for the 105th playing of this storied Major ultimately won by Brooks Koepka.

programme.title: PGA Championship Film 2024
programme.desc: This is the story of 2024 PGA Championship from Valhalla Golf Club, the scene of Xander Schauffele's first Major championship win.

programme.title: Roots: Shane Lowry
programme.desc: Hear directly from the Irish golfer Shane Lowry and from those who know him best about the highs and lows of his career to date.

programme.title: U.S. Open Golf Official Film 1999
programme.desc: A chance to relive the 1999 US Open at the Pinehurst in North Carolina, which featured an unforgettable conclusion on the final day.

programme.title: U.S. Open Golf Official Film 2000
programme.desc: Remember the 2000 US Open, held at Pebble Beach Golf Links. A golfing superstar would take home the title, breaking a Major record in the process.

programme.title: U.S. Open Golf Official Film 2001
programme.desc: Producing one of the wildest endings in championship history, the 2001 US Open at Southern Hills Country Club in Tulsa, Oklahoma, was one to remember.

programme.title: U.S. Open Golf Official Film 2002
programme.desc: The official film of the 2002 US Open chronicles a memorable week on Long Island, as the 2000 champion Tiger Woods displayed his prowess once more in golf's ultimate test.

programme.title: U.S. Open Golf Official Film 2003
programme.desc: The official film of the 2003 US Open, a year in which Jim Furyk put on one of the best scoring displays in the championship's history.

programme.title: U.S. Open Golf Official Film 2004
programme.desc: A chance to relive the 2004 US Open at Shinnecock Hills Golf Club in New York. A former champion would win this tournament for the second time.

programme.title: U.S. Open Golf Official Film 2008
programme.desc: Ahead of the US Open, the year's second golf major, take a look back to 2008 with the official film of the tournament. Argentina's Angel Cabrera was the defending champion from 2007.

programme.title: Live PL: Everton v Brentford
programme.desc: Coming away 2-0 winners from the City Ground, Everton are back at the Hill Dickinson Stadium for a Premier League encounter with Keith Andrews' in-form Brentford.

programme.title: Mcllroy '25: A Career Year
programme.desc: A look at an unprecedented year in the career of the newly minted Grand Slam champion Rory McIlroy, who finally ended his wait for an illustrious Green Jacket during the 2025 season.

programme.title: Justin Rose Junior Championship
programme.desc: Highlights from the finals of the 2025 Justin Rose Telegraph Junior Golf Championship - one of the UK's leading youth tournaments held at Quinta do Lago in Portugal.

programme.title: U.S. Open Golf Official Film 2011

programme.title: TGL Golf M2: Boston C v LA GC
programme.desc: Rory McIlroy's Boston Common Golf Club compete in TGL action at the SoFi Center against Justin Rose and Tommy Fleetwood's Los Angeles Golf Club.

programme.title: U.S. Open Golf Official Film 2013

programme.title: U.S. Open Golf Official Film 2014
programme.desc: The story of the 2014 US Open Championship at the No. 2 Course of the Pinehurst Resort in North Carolina. England's Justin Rose came into this event as the defending champion.

programme.title: U.S. Open Golf Official Film 2015
programme.desc: The official film of the 2015 US Open, one of golf's four majors. Martin Kaymer went in as the defending champion from 2014.

programme.title: U.S. Open Golf Official Film 2016
